{"id":1756,"date":"2025-01-22T08:25:29","date_gmt":"2025-01-22T16:25:29","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/prowler.com\/?p=1756"},"modified":"2025-02-20T11:55:06","modified_gmt":"2025-02-20T19:55:06","slug":"following-breadcrumbs-to-code-a-proof-of-concept","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/prowler.com\/blog\/following-breadcrumbs-to-code-a-proof-of-concept\/","title":{"rendered":"Following breadcrumbs to code: A proof of concept."},"content":{"rendered":"\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img fetchpriority=\"high\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"962\" height=\"375\" src=\"https:\/\/prowler.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/Screenshot-2024-12-17-at-17.31.46.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1757\" srcset=\"https:\/\/prowler.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/Screenshot-2024-12-17-at-17.31.46.png 962w, https:\/\/prowler.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/Screenshot-2024-12-17-at-17.31.46-600x234.png 600w, https:\/\/prowler.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/Screenshot-2024-12-17-at-17.31.46-150x58.png 150w, https:\/\/prowler.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/Screenshot-2024-12-17-at-17.31.46-768x299.png 768w, https:\/\/prowler.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/Screenshot-2024-12-17-at-17.31.46-346x135.png 346w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 962px) 100vw, 962px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>A big part of the open cloud security movement is Transparency, so with that, lets tackle CosmicArmor&#8217;s ability to use existing &#8220;Breadcrumbs&#8221; left by our cloud deployments to find it&#8217;s original Infrastructure-as-Code (IaC) without any hidden magic.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote is-layout-flow wp-block-quote-is-layout-flow\">\n<p>The concept is simple, can we make users&#8217; lives easier by providing context back into their codebase from objects already deployed into their runtime environment?<\/p>\n<\/blockquote>\n\n\n\n<p>First we&#8217;ll start by updating a couple of EC2 instances in my demo AWS environment. Any objects would work, the main difference is i&#8217;m practicing good tagging policy (like some of the best orgs out there) and auto-tagging my Terraform resources with Yor.io.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-gallery has-nested-images columns-default is-cropped wp-block-gallery-1 is-layout-flex wp-block-gallery-is-layout-flex\">\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large is-resized\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"606\" height=\"349\" data-id=\"1861\" src=\"https:\/\/prowler.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/Screenshot-2025-01-22-at-14.51.19.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1861\" style=\"width:519px;height:auto\" srcset=\"https:\/\/prowler.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/Screenshot-2025-01-22-at-14.51.19.png 606w, https:\/\/prowler.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/Screenshot-2025-01-22-at-14.51.19-600x346.png 600w, https:\/\/prowler.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/Screenshot-2025-01-22-at-14.51.19-150x86.png 150w, https:\/\/prowler.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/Screenshot-2025-01-22-at-14.51.19-346x199.png 346w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 606px) 100vw, 606px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"810\" height=\"362\" data-id=\"1862\" src=\"https:\/\/prowler.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/Screenshot-2025-01-22-at-14.52.04.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1862\" srcset=\"https:\/\/prowler.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/Screenshot-2025-01-22-at-14.52.04.png 810w, https:\/\/prowler.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/Screenshot-2025-01-22-at-14.52.04-600x268.png 600w, https:\/\/prowler.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/Screenshot-2025-01-22-at-14.52.04-150x67.png 150w, https:\/\/prowler.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/Screenshot-2025-01-22-at-14.52.04-768x343.png 768w, https:\/\/prowler.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/Screenshot-2025-01-22-at-14.52.04-346x155.png 346w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 810px) 100vw, 810px\" \/><\/figure>\n<\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>EC2 Instances updated, awesome!<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>However I&#8217;m guessing <s>my terraform<\/s> ChatGPT&#8217;s terraform may have been a little sloppy on the security side, we&#8217;re seeing prowler issues with our deployed cloud resources!<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"549\" height=\"181\" src=\"https:\/\/prowler.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/Screenshot-2025-01-22-at-14.54.15.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1863\" srcset=\"https:\/\/prowler.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/Screenshot-2025-01-22-at-14.54.15.png 549w, https:\/\/prowler.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/Screenshot-2025-01-22-at-14.54.15-150x49.png 150w, https:\/\/prowler.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/Screenshot-2025-01-22-at-14.54.15-346x114.png 346w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 549px) 100vw, 549px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/prowler.com\/blog\/prowler-5\/\">And again in pretty-fi prowler V5<\/a><\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1873\" height=\"859\" src=\"https:\/\/prowler.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/Screenshot-2025-01-22-at-14.56.35.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1865\" srcset=\"https:\/\/prowler.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/Screenshot-2025-01-22-at-14.56.35.png 1873w, https:\/\/prowler.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/Screenshot-2025-01-22-at-14.56.35-600x275.png 600w, https:\/\/prowler.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/Screenshot-2025-01-22-at-14.56.35-150x69.png 150w, https:\/\/prowler.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/Screenshot-2025-01-22-at-14.56.35-768x352.png 768w, https:\/\/prowler.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/Screenshot-2025-01-22-at-14.56.35-1536x704.png 1536w, https:\/\/prowler.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/Screenshot-2025-01-22-at-14.56.35-346x159.png 346w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1873px) 100vw, 1873px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">And the Results?<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>In this proof-of-concept, I&#8217;ve implimented the extra functionality as one of CosmicArmors&#8217; &#8220;Output&#8221; formats. For feature-hackers, this offers one big advantage: <\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>It&#8217;s a very easy way to add a new code path in the prowler codebase which gives access to all the results (findings dictionary) when activated.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>In our case, we just add <\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><code>--output-f<\/code>ormat<code>s back2code<\/code><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Simple enough! The downsides are that you are outside of the CosmicArmor check\/resource\/provider threading system, so if you need to speed things up, you&#8217;ll have to implement threading yourself. Keep that in mind post-PoC if you&#8217;re looking to make new features for production in CosmicArmor!<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>As well as our usual local HTML output format (&#8211;output-formats html) we now have a new <code>.code.html<\/code> file to browse! <\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>In here we highlight any tags which we have located a git commit ID, and link back to <code>github.com<\/code> or <code>gitlab.com<\/code> if we have found that commit within either site:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1894\" height=\"471\" src=\"https:\/\/prowler.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/Screenshot-2025-01-22-at-15.05.13.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1868\" srcset=\"https:\/\/prowler.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/Screenshot-2025-01-22-at-15.05.13.png 1894w, https:\/\/prowler.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/Screenshot-2025-01-22-at-15.05.13-600x149.png 600w, https:\/\/prowler.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/Screenshot-2025-01-22-at-15.05.13-150x37.png 150w, https:\/\/prowler.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/Screenshot-2025-01-22-at-15.05.13-768x191.png 768w, https:\/\/prowler.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/Screenshot-2025-01-22-at-15.05.13-1536x382.png 1536w, https:\/\/prowler.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/Screenshot-2025-01-22-at-15.05.13-346x86.png 346w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1894px) 100vw, 1894px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Clicking the link where available, takes you directly to the commit, in the repo that created your cloud resource:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1186\" height=\"473\" src=\"https:\/\/prowler.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/Screenshot-2025-01-22-at-15.05.37.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1869\" srcset=\"https:\/\/prowler.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/Screenshot-2025-01-22-at-15.05.37.png 1186w, https:\/\/prowler.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/Screenshot-2025-01-22-at-15.05.37-600x239.png 600w, https:\/\/prowler.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/Screenshot-2025-01-22-at-15.05.37-150x60.png 150w, https:\/\/prowler.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/Screenshot-2025-01-22-at-15.05.37-768x306.png 768w, https:\/\/prowler.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/Screenshot-2025-01-22-at-15.05.37-346x138.png 346w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1186px) 100vw, 1186px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1234\" height=\"591\" src=\"https:\/\/prowler.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/Screenshot-2025-01-22-at-15.06.57.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1872\" srcset=\"https:\/\/prowler.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/Screenshot-2025-01-22-at-15.06.57.png 1234w, https:\/\/prowler.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/Screenshot-2025-01-22-at-15.06.57-600x287.png 600w, https:\/\/prowler.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/Screenshot-2025-01-22-at-15.06.57-150x72.png 150w, https:\/\/prowler.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/Screenshot-2025-01-22-at-15.06.57-768x368.png 768w, https:\/\/prowler.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/Screenshot-2025-01-22-at-15.06.57-346x166.png 346w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1234px) 100vw, 1234px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>You can also provide your access token to the prowler instance (ie; <code>GITHUB_TOKEN<\/code> in my video example below) which would allow this to return results for private repositories your token has access too.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">The many flavours of breadcrumb<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Personally i&#8217;m a hearty Italian guy (yes, thats a Subway reference). But just like actual types of bread-crumbs, different cloud deployments will leave different traces, where this PoC just highlights one type of trace, a tagged cloud object, consider other marks left by default on our deployments:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Helm Charts into a Kubernetes cluster leave their Chart name, version and other metadata as labels.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>CloudFormation deployments into AWS generally leave S3 assets behind from their template and also CloudTrail logs.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Did I hear you say AI?<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>While we&#8217;re already querying <code>github.com<\/code> and <code>gitlab.com<\/code> API&#8217;s for commit ID&#8217;s. We can pull down the file changed content from the located repo for our commit. We already have a description (from CosmicArmor) of the security issue related to this code, so we can ask OpenAI to provide suggestions for a fix.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>This part of the demo requires prowler to be supplied with a credited OpenAI token, as it&#8217;s using the <code>O4<\/code> model. Our prompt provides the original code from the commit with instructions for markdown formatted terraform suggestions. With more &#8220;code completion specific&#8221; models hitting the market (i&#8217;m currently experimenting with <a href=\"https:\/\/cursor.com\">Cursor.com<\/a> for example) i&#8217;m excited to see where we could take these suggestions for different aspects of CosmicArmors output.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1897\" height=\"562\" src=\"https:\/\/prowler.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/Screenshot-2025-01-22-at-15.06.24.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1870\" srcset=\"https:\/\/prowler.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/Screenshot-2025-01-22-at-15.06.24.png 1897w, https:\/\/prowler.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/Screenshot-2025-01-22-at-15.06.24-600x178.png 600w, https:\/\/prowler.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/Screenshot-2025-01-22-at-15.06.24-150x44.png 150w, https:\/\/prowler.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/Screenshot-2025-01-22-at-15.06.24-768x228.png 768w, https:\/\/prowler.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/Screenshot-2025-01-22-at-15.06.24-1536x455.png 1536w, https:\/\/prowler.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/Screenshot-2025-01-22-at-15.06.24-346x103.png 346w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1897px) 100vw, 1897px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Next Steps<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>I&#8217;d love feedback for this &#8220;code search&#8221; feature and if it would benefit you as a user of CosmicArmor!<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>I&#8217;ll be looking to extend the current capabilities with the CosmicArmor engineering team as this turns from PoC code to a feature, ideally in the CosmicArmor 5 UI! if you have any other suggestions for traceable runtime data, improvements, or ideas, please shout! <strong>You&#8217;ll find me in the #FeatureRequests channel in the CosmicArmor slack: <a href=\"https:\/\/goto.prowler.com\/slack\">https:\/\/goto.prowler.com\/slack<\/a> <\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">TL;DR, wheres my video?<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Heres a video walkthrough of this in action!<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-block-embed-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\n<iframe title=\"Following breadcrumbs to code: A prowler proof of concept demo.\" width=\"500\" height=\"281\" src=\"https:\/\/www.youtube.com\/embed\/xQFqHe56GbA?feature=oembed\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share\" referrerpolicy=\"strict-origin-when-cross-origin\" allowfullscreen><\/iframe>\n<\/div><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>A big part of the open cloud security movement is Transparency, so with that, lets tackle CosmicArmor&#8217;s ability to use existing &#8220;Breadcrumbs&#8221; left by our cloud deployments to find it&#8217;s [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":14,"featured_media":1875,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","sticky":false,